### Because NAs in these features are not by random, NA represent absence of a garage in the property##
data$GarageType <- as.character(data$GarageType)
data$GarageType[which(is.na(data$GarageType))]<-"None"
data$GarageType<-as.factor(data$GarageType)

data$GarageYrBlt[which(is.na(data$GarageYrBlt))] <- 0

data$GarageFinish <- as.character(data$GarageFinish)
data$GarageFinish[which(is.na(data$GarageFinish))] <- "None"
data$GarageFinish <- as.factor(data$GarageFinish)

data$GarageQual <- as.character(data$GarageQual)
data$GarageQual[which(is.na(data$GarageQual))] <- "None"
data$GarageQual <- as.factor(data$GarageQual)

data$GarageCond <- as.character(data$GarageCond)
data$GarageCond[which(is.na(data$GarageCond))] <- "None"
data$GarageCond <- as.factor(data$GarageCond)

###NAs in FirePlaceType are because of no fireplaces in the property 
data$FireplaceQu <- as.character(data$FireplaceQu)
data$FireplaceQu[which(is.na(data$FireplaceQu))] <- "None"
data$FireplaceQu <- as.factor(data$FireplaceQu)

#No Masonry Veneer type
data$MasVnrType <- as.character(data$MasVnrType)
data$MasVnrType[which(is.na(data$MasVnrType))] <- "None"
data$MasVnrType <- as.factor(data$MasVnrType)


##Basement : NA means no basement present in the property

data$BsmtQual <- as.character(data$BsmtQual)
data$BsmtQual[which(is.na(data$BsmtQual))] <- "None"
data$BsmtQual <- as.factor(data$BsmtQual)

data$BsmtCond <- as.character(data$BsmtCond)
data$BsmtCond[which(is.na(data$BsmtCond))] <- "None"
data$BsmtCond <- as.factor(data$BsmtCond)

data$BsmtExposure <- as.character(data$BsmtExposure)
data$BsmtExposure[which(is.na(data$BsmtExposure))] <- "None"
data$BsmtExposure <- as.factor(data$BsmtExposure)

data$BsmtFinType1 <- as.character(data$BsmtFinType1)
data$BsmtFinType1[which(is.na(data$BsmtFinType1))] <- "None"
data$BsmtFinType1 <- as.factor(data$BsmtFinType1)

data$BsmtFinType2 <- as.character(data$BsmtFinType2)
data$BsmtFinType2[which(is.na(data$BsmtFinType2))] <- "None"
data$BsmtFinType2 <- as.factor(data$BsmtFinType2)

### Combining Variables ###

data$TotBathrooms <- data$FullBath + (data$HalfBath*0.5) + data$BsmtFullBath + (data$BsmtHalfBath*0.5)
data$TotalSqFeet <- data$GrLivArea + data$TotalBsmtSF + data$GarageArea
data$TotalPorchSF <- data$OpenPorchSF + data$EnclosedPorch + data$X3SsnPorch + data$ScreenPorch


## Adding new Variables ##

data$PropAge <- data$YrSold - data$YearBuilt
data$Remod <- ifelse(data$YearBuilt==data$YearRemodAdd, 0, 1) #0=No Remodeling, 1=Remodeling
data$LastRemod <- as.numeric(data$YrSold)-data$YearRemodAdd
data$IsNew <- ifelse(data$YrSold - data$YearBuilt < 15, 1, 0)

###Converting Numerical values into factors

data$MoSold<-as.factor(data$MoSold)
data$YrSold<-as.factor(data$YrSold)
data$MSSubClass<-as.factor(data$MSSubClass)

data$Street<-NULL

## Factorizing
data<-data %>% 
  mutate_if(is.character, as.factor)

## Remove other low-variance variables
data <- data[,-(nearZeroVar(data, freqCut = 98/2, uniqueCut = 2))]



##Imputation

mfimp <- missForest(data)
